qas.question: Who won power after Ed Miliband?
What did Miliband want to change the balance of the UK economy towards?
What did Miliband want to regulate less?

context: <b1_0>Harriet Harman<b1_0/> became the Leader of the Opposition and acting Leader of the Labour Party following the resignation of Gordon Brown on <b0_0>11 May 2010<b0_0/>, pending a leadership election subsequently won by Ed Miliband. Miliband emphasised "<b2_0>responsible capitalism<b2_0/>" and greater state intervention to change the balance of the UK economy away from <b3_0>financial services<b3_0/>. Tackling vested interests and opening up closed circles in British society were also themes he returned to a number of times. Miliband also argued for greater regulation on <b4_0>banks<b4_0/> and the energy companies.
